package.name: Horde_Util
package.description: A library that provides functionality useful for all kind of applications.

release.notes: * Initial release as a PEAR package
* Converted to package.xml 2.0 for pear.horde.org

* Added magic PHP5 methods to the Variables class. * Added array_merge_recursive_overwrite() to Horde_Array(). * Fixed a bug in Horde_Array::arraySort where auto-detecting the first key failed. * Added sorter functions for array keys. * Removed use of array_unique(). * Cleaned up addParameter() in the Util class. * Implemented a much more efficient, yet safer file wiping algorithm. * Fixed Util::addParameter when it is passed a base URL that contains an urlencoded ampersand. * Added a parameter to Util::nocacheUrl() to not encode url. * Added Util::getPathInfo(). * Signed parameters to go.php with an HMAC based on a new secret key configuration value, to prevent using go.php as an open referrer. * Made logout tokens only valid for a configurable length of time. * Made it possible to use String.php without having any other files available. * Use utf8_decode() in String::length() if possible. * Always use preg_match() in String::regexMatch(). * Workaround for korean messages in a non-standard charset. * Fixed String::substr() length calculations. * Added multibyte-safe String::wordwrap() method. * Added parameter to use wordwrap() for line folding. * Use C as the portable locale (Bug #6194). * Don't use utf8_encode/decode on very large strings if other options are available. (Bug #6660) * Fixed order of checks in String::convertCharset (Bug #6794).

* First alpha release for Horde 4. * Added Horde_String::rpos(). * Renamed Horde_Array::array_merge_recursive_overwrite() to Horde_Array::replaceRecursive(). * Added Horde_String::common(). * Added Horde_Domhtml::. * Removed Horde_Util::assertDriverConfig(). * Removed Horde_Util::bufferOutput(). * Removed Horde_Util::uriB64Encode() and Horde_Util::uriB64Decode(). * Removed Horde_Util::strftime2date() and Horde_Util::date2strftime(). * Removed Horde_Util::closeWindowJs() and Horde_Util::nocacheUrl(). * Added Horde_String::convertToUtf8(). * Added Horde_Util::abbreviate(). * Removed Horde_Array::combine() and Horde_Util::hmac().
* First beta release for Horde 4.
* First release candidate for Horde 4. * [mms] Tweak loading HTML documents (encodings) in Horde_Domhtml. * [mms] Added Horde_Domhtml#returnBody(). * [mms] Added Domhtml unit tests.
* Second release candidate for Horde 4. * Fix parsing ISO-8859-15 data with Horde_Domhtml (Bug #9714).
* First stable release for Horde 4.
* [jan] Fix wrapping of several follow-up lines with existing line breaks. * [jan] Fix creating temporary files with open_basedir restrictions.
* [mms] In Horde_Variables, operate on a copy of the $_REQUEST variable.
* [mms] Don't try to use dl() in PHP 5.3+.
* [jan] Unescape escaped quotes when importing CSV data.
* [jan] Fix removing too many backslashes with magic quotes enabled (Bug #10149). * [jan] Fix reading CSV data with PHP < 5.3.
* [jan] Speed up Horde_String::substr() (Evert Pot, Request #8627).
* [mms] Add Horde_String::validUtf8().
* [mms] Add Horde_Variables#filter().
* [jan] Implement ArrayAccess in Horde_Variables.
* [mms] Fix Horde_String::validUtf8() to workaround PHP/PCRE bug where segfault will occur on input strings > ~5000 characters
* [mms] Add Horde_String::trimUtf8Bom().

* First alpha release for Horde 5. * [mms] Removed e-mail array manipulation methods (Horde_Mail package now provides this feature). * [mms] Removed Horde_Util::getCsv() (moved to Horde_Data package). * [mms] Add iteration to Horde_Domhtml object. * [jan] Remove Horde_Util::getTempDir(). * [jan] Remove Horde_Array::replaceRecursive().
* First beta release for Horde 5.
* [mms] Remove Horde_Util::addParameter() and Horde_Util::removeParameter(). * [mms] Remove Horde_Util::cloneObject().
* First stable release for Horde 5.
* [mms] Use new Horde_Test layout.
* [mms] Convert Horde_String#validUtf8() from a preg-regex to a string iterator to eliminate PCRE issues relating to stack sizes (Bug #11899).
* [mms] Fix validating certain strings of UTF-8 data (Bug #11930).

* [mms] Added 'charset' and 'metacharset' parameters to returnHtml(). * [mms] Added Horde_Domhtml#getCharset() to get best-guess charset of current encoding within the DOM object. * [mms] Fix inserting HEAD into HTML document with Horde_Domhtml#getHead() if it doesn't already exist in the document.
* [mms] Can't add charset directly to HTML document or else DOM will alter document when generating HTML. * [mms] Added Horde_Domhtml#getBody().
* [mms] Simplify Horde_Variables iterator.
* [mms] Fix Horde_Domhtml#returnBody().
* [mms] SECURITY: '_formvars' form input must now be JSON encoded, not PHP serialized.
* [mms] Add Horde_String_Transliterate class. * [mms] Support deeply nested HTML documents (requires PHP 5.4.0+ and libxml 2.7.0+) (Bug #13086).
* [mms] Fallback to lesser priority transliterator driver when an error is encountered.
* [mms] Fix regression in Horde_String_Transliterate for PHP 5.3 (Bug #13419). * [mms] Added Horde_String::ipos() and Horde_String::ripos().
* [mms] Fix another issue with older versions of PHP in Horde_String_Transliterate.
* [mms] Fix deleting multi-level temporary directories in Horde_Util::deleteAtShutdown().
* [jan] Use grapheme functions in Horde_String if intl extension is available.
* [mms] Fix error detection when using Horde_String::substr() with mb_substr().
* [mms] Fix handling broken text input with all multibyte drivers.
* [jan] Fix test that could fail due to changes in glibc. * [jan] Fix Composer file.
* [jan] Mark PHP 7 as supported.
* [mjr] Fix detecting certain types of broken UTF-8 strings.
* [mjr] PHP 7.4 compatibility fixes (Remi Collet <remi@famillecollet.com>, PR #2). * [jan] Fix wrapping if the wrapping break adds indention.
* [mjr] Silence deprecation notices for PHP 8.1 tentative return types (PR #8). * [jan] Fix error with invalid charsets on PHP 8 (Ralf Becker <RalfBecker@outdoor-training.de>, PR #5).
* [mjr] Fix deprecation warning when passing null to strtolower (PR #9). * |+
* [mjr] PHP 7.4 compatibility fixes (Remi Collet <remi@famillecollet.com>, PR #2). * [jan] Fix wrapping if the wrapping break adds indention.
* [rla] Enable PHP 8, add namespaced version
